 must be transparent, neutral, and fair, with every proposal justifiably enhancing the governance artifacts' strength in alignment with Universal Alignment, as outlined in A.1.5.2. In essence, the AVC must balance the present needs with future foresight, ensuring that governance strategies and scope proposals not only address immediate concerns but also fortify the governance structure against future misalignment risks, as per the guidance provided in A.1.5.8. \"Long-term Alignment Artifact Strength\" is a pivotal element in the fabric of NEWDAO's governance, demanding a proactive, forward-thinking approach from AVCs. It requires AVCs to act as custodians of the governance framework, ensuring that every decision made today will stand the test of time and continue to serve the NEWDAO ecosystem faithfully and effectively in the pursuit of its mission and vision."
